column3: Average amount of belief per plan context
column4: Average amount of operations per plan body
column5: Amount of generated plans which are general/specific (roughly: using variables or not)
column8: Amount of generated plans which are useless (e.g., not executable at runtime because subsumed my more general plans, etc.)
column9: Number of plans which are correctly converted in JaKtA
column10: Amount of inadequate usage of admissible goals: not properly written, invented but not used, used but not admissible, already admissible
column11: Amount of inadequate usage of admissible beliefs: not properly written, invented but not used, used but not admissible, already admissible
column12: Amount of inadequate usage of actions
column13: Cosine distance of generated plans group w.r.t. minimal, human-derived plans group
column14: Time to goal achievement for the generated plan groups who work (in seconds) (maybe normalized w.r.t. the minimal human-generated plan)
